Writing a function to perform bootstrap

library(boot)
## 
## Attaching package: 'boot'
## The following object is masked from 'package:car':
## 
##     logit
bs <- function(formula, data, indices) {
    d <- data[indices,]
    fit <- lm(d$logHomeRange~d$logFemaleMass, data=d)
    return(coef(fit))
}

results <- boot(data=d, statistic=bs, R=1000, formula=d$logHomeRange~d$logFemaleMass)

results
## 
## ORDINARY NONPARAMETRIC BOOTSTRAP
## 
## 
## Call:
## boot(data = d, statistic = bs, R = 1000, formula = d$logHomeRange ~ 
##     d$logFemaleMass)
## 
## 
## Bootstrap Statistics :
##      original       bias    std. error
## t1* -9.441231 -0.034753794  0.61416218
## t2*  1.036432  0.004092406  0.07841339
plot(results, index=1) # intercept

plot(results, index=2) # wt

# get 95% confidence intervals
boot.ci(results, type="bca", index=1) # intercept
